title: For Sale:  S&W Model 915 9mm/ Case/ 3 mags
postcontent:
Selling an older style Smith & Wesson 3rd Generation Model 915, which is the less fancy version of their Model 5904. The 915 is basically the very same, rock solid, dead nuts reliable pistol w/ the same milled steel internal parts as the 5904 in a more 'utilitarian' form & was an iconic gun with many law enforcement agencies during the 1990's... sort of like what the Model 28 Highway Patrolman .357 magnum was to the shinier Model 27 revolver in previous decades.
 Read the reviews if you are unfamiliar with this pistol; but if you want accuracy, function, and high capacity in a great all-around 9mm for not a lot of cash- you'll never go wrong with a 915. 
 This gun is mechanically excellent, very smooth action (double & single), and very tight & light due to it's quality alloy frame. It does have some slight carry wear on the edges, and a few tiny nicks in the finish, but still looks great & always shoot like a champ with any ammo.
 It comes in a S&W case that fits it great- (but was originally for an M&P), & has (3) 15 rnd. factory mags, & a Pachmayer finger-groove slip-on grip. I'm asking $400 for the pkg. but will add a very nice hand boned brown Don Hume shoulder holster rig with mag pouches for an additional $100. I think the holster was made for a SIG 9mm, but it fits this gun just as well.
 This is a very high quality pistol that many LE officers, (as well as many other folks), have bet their lives on in the past, and will continue to be a great bet for a long, long time. Nothin' fancy- just a great little 9mm workhorse.  S&W got it right with these older autos and they have earned their excellent reputation among the shooting community. Let me know if you need more info.                                                        Thanks

title: For Sale/Trade:  S&W m1917 WWI US Military issue .45 ACP revolver, Early Production.
postcontent:
The original .45 ACP moonclip revolver, this S&W model of 1917 was likely manufactured in 1918, but other than the fine vintage craftsmanship, it looks much much newer.  Standard military issue 5.5" barrel, blade sights, lanyard ring, and has all the military hallmarks and govt. property stamps. 

The m1917 revolver is in great shape.  It is a real US Army issue piece from WWI -- not one of the less valuable Brazilian issue guns.  These guys go from $1000-$2500 on gunbroker, and are a good investment or collector piece as well as being fun to shoot.

This gun is wearing a set of valuable and sought after "diamond" grips with inset brass S&W escutcheons.  These grips may or may not be original to the gun (official sources disagree on this point), but they are period correct for the teens and 20s, and look really sharp. 

Comes with a bunch of full and half moonclips.

Historical Details: 
Smith & Wesson produced approximately 169,595 U.S. Army Model 1917 Revolvers between 1917 and 1919. The first contract WAR-ORD-14451-R31 was dated August 8th, 1917 for 100,000 revolvers at $14.75 each.  This was the first of two contracts to provide Model 1917s to the U.S. Army. 

This example has the ordnance acceptance mark of GHS (Col. Gilbert H. Stewart) which is only seen on approximately the first 40,000 revolvers produced -- less then 25% of the S&W M1917 revolvers have the GHS stamp.  The butt is marked “US Army Model 1917- No 35XXX”. This very early production has the better commercial style finish from earlier in production when they were still taking their time and making 'em right.

Effortless Charging 
No more fumbling with messy cables. No more breaking delicate connectors. No more hassle. Just plug the station into a wall outlet, forget about it and the next time the battery runs low, drop it to charge. Form follows function, and that can be seen in our unobtrusive charging plate, elegant stand, attention-grabbing sound speaker or surprising headset design. 
The first of our wireless charging accessory range is the Nokia Wireless Charging Plate DT-900. This thin slate will become the new “home” for your Smartphones – at home, at the office, wherever there’s a stable and flat surface waiting – so they can relieve themselves of the worry of drained batteries. 
Its design matches not only the award-winning Lumia device range, but looks (and works) with other Smartphones lying on top of it. 
The DT-900 comes in a variety of colors intended to either blend into its surroundings or boldly stand out. Once plugged into a nearby outlet, the DT-900 charges on contact with Qi-enabled wireless charging products, whether produced by Nokia or other manufacturers. 
Our range of wireless charging accessories comes with a large charging surface which means there is no need for precise alignment between phone and charger. 
Wire coils found inside compatible products receive power when they come near charging stations, recharging batteries with efficiency rates rivaling the average wired charger (in fact, it’s over 80% as efficient). Even though the coils and station never actually come into physical contact (as the back cover remains between them), energy flows and recharging happens when the two are in close proximity (typical range of 3mm). This technology is called “inductive” or “closely coupled” charging. 
All of our wireless charging products also feature the latest advances in Foreign Object Detection, which means they don’t become active if someone accidentally drops keys, paper clips or any object that’s not specifically designed to be charged wirelessly.

title: For Sale:  COLT 1911 GCNM Series 80 MK IV SS 'Enhanced' .45
postcontent:
This gun has a pretty long title, name, designation (or whatever)- so stay with me here....
It's a 'Colt 1911/Series 80/ Mark IV/ Gold Cup National Match/ Stainless Steel/ 'Enhanced Version'/ in .45 ACP'. 
Whew!
 In spite of; (or maybe BECAUSE?) of all that- it's a great Colt 1911.
The 'Enhanced' version of the Cold Cup Nat'l. Match guns were only produced for a short span back in the 1990s, & are kind of scarce. They have the ribbed barrel, an undercut frame, & some other features that make them unique among 1911s....I'm no 1911 expert, but I really like the feel & function this gun. It's a target pistol, so it's very accurate (duh) too. One thing I did change was the flat main spring housing, (original is polymer), with an Ed Brown arched type. title: For Sale:  The Ultimate Christmas Present for Lovers of Unique Guns
postcontent:
I have for sale (or possibly trade) a  completely original, WW2 German Walther type P-38 "Luger Pistole." It is completely original, unrestored and in gorgeous condition. It does have its original Bakelite grips. Manufactured by Spreewerke GmbH in Germany during the war for officers of the Wehrmacht. All numbers match and all of the correct Wehrmacht stamps are in place. It does have the original and correct magazine. 

These were exceedingly robust and reliable guns. They were one of the most prized souvenirs of the returning GI's that were lucky enough to confiscate one before they returned stateside. Perfect gun for a WW2 collector or just anyone that loves the beauty of German Engineering.

title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense  10.3" 5.56mm Carbine,1:7, Government Profile
postcontent:
Cold Hammer Forging of barrels has been known for decades to produce the most accurate, longest lasting rifle barrels obtainable. The Cold Hammer Forging of barrels is accomplished through intense hydraulic pressure applied at opposing angles by carbide steel hammers. During the hammering process, a mandrel is inserted into the bore while the carbide steel hammers shape the barrel around the mandrel creating the chamber, the lands, and the grooves. In addition to the aforementioned benefits, the Cold Hammer Forging process creates a defect free bore and the most consistent chamber possible.
All Daniel Defense cold hammer forged barrels are made from start to finish in our state-of-the-art facility located in Black Creek, GA. In keeping with our heritage of not cutting corners, all cold hammer forged barrels feature a forged chamber and heavy phosphate exterior coating. They are all MP tested on-site and are available in multiple configurations which includes barrel only (stripped); barrel with front sight base; barrel with Low Profile Gas Block; and barrel with front sight base, gas tube, and delta ring assembly (Complete). These barrels will prove themselves to be more accurate and last longer than a barrel that has cut or button rifling.

title: For Sale/Trade:  FACTORY FOLDER Ruger Mini 14 .223 W/ Paratrooper Stock Trade for Collector P08 Luger
postcontent:
If you are reading this, the Mini is still available. Pictures available for serious buyers upon request.

I am a collector looking to trade my prized rifle for an equally valuable collector-grade Luger Pistol. I am specifically seeking a pre- 1939 pistol with all matching numbers. I prefer the looks of the 8" barrel LP08 artillery luger but will consider very nice 4" standard models or 6" navy models. No modern production pistols. Extra long Commercial lengths may be considered. Commercial or Military issue are both welcomed. 9mm only. (Sorry 7.65 fans) I will consider refinished pistols if they were done extremely well and appear in 98%+ condition. A gun with nickel finish may be considered in perfect condition with matching #'s. No rust, minimal pitting, and 100% functionality are a must. No Russian captures or import markings- must be a WWI or WWII vet bring-back. The ideal pistol I am looking for would be a 1916-1918 DWM P08 or LP08 in 85%+ condition. A pistol that grandpa brought back from the war and was kept in a trunk for 70 years and rarely took out of the holster. Maybe you inherited one and want something with a bit more firepower and just as much cool factor and range appeal. 

To trade, I have a 1985 Ruger Mini-14 with the factory original walnut side-folding paratrooper stock. It is simply awesome. The original owner purchased the gun new from a dealer in California in 1985, fired 20 rounds through it in 1986, cleaned it meticulously and stored it in his closet. I purchased it and have fired 70 rounds through it just last month, cleaned it meticulously and stored it as well. So total round count is guaranteed at under 100. It is in 99%+ condition. Perfect bluing with matching blued stock (much rarer than the stainless model), perfect wood, perfect screws, mirror bore, and the lightest marks from racking the action and folding and latching the stock. It could easily be passed for brand new never fired condition. It is an absolute dream to shoot and makes pretty 2" groups at 100 yards shooting PMC 55gr .223. Marked .223 caliber, but manual says it can fire 5.56 as well. It would make a great Christmas present for yourself.

The stock alone normally sells for $650 if you can find one in brand new condition. The gun itself is valued at at least $950 in the current market. I am also including a new synthetic side folding stock valued at $120 and a vintage 80's mossy oak camo hunting stock valued at $40. Also included is a new green nylon sling, one police surplus 20 round magazine, one new 30 round magazine, and two new 40 round magazines valued at $30-$40 each. In a retail setting, this is close to a $2,000 package. The gun itself with original stock books at over $1400. I am looking to trade for a very nice Luger pistol only, which would itself is valued at between $1,300 and $2,000. This would ideally be a straight across trade, gun for gun. Cash on your end if your Luger isn't in very good shape. I will be willing to flex on overall condition for especially collectable models (like artillery models or very early dates or with holster and extra magazines) If you think you may have a pistol I would be interested in, please send detailed pictures in an Email. The worst I can say is: "No, thank you. Have a nice day."

Cash offer on the package of $1,800. Lowball cash offers will not receive a response. A plethora of high resolution pictures of the Mini are available for serious buyers. Viewing can be arranged in early mornings Monday-Friday and Weekends. Cash or Luger trade only face to face, here in Arlington, Washington State. Meeting only at the Norpoint shooting range. I will not travel unless to trade. No shipping; no FFL transfers. This gun is not for sale anywhere else and has never been offered for sale before.

I respond to Emails promptly. Please, for the sake of continuity and clarity, no phone communications until pickup is arranged.

Thanks for looking!
